Subject: [PATCH net-next ct-offload v3 08/15] net/mlx5: E-Switch, Introduce global tables
Date:   Wed, 11 Mar 2020 16:33:51 +0200
Message-Id: <1583937238-21511-9-git-send-email-paulb@mellanox.com>
X-Mailer: git-send-email 1.8.4.3
In-Reply-To: <1583937238-21511-1-git-send-email-paulb@mellanox.com>
References: <1583937238-21511-1-git-send-email-paulb@mellanox.com>
Sender: netdev-owner@vger.kernel.org
Precedence: bulk
List-ID: <netdev.vger.kernel.org>
X-Mailing-List: netdev@vger.kernel.org

Currently, flow tables are automatically connected according to their
<chain,prio,level> tuple.

Introduce global tables which are flow tables that are detached from the
eswitch chains processing, and will be connected by explicitly referencing
them from multiple chains.

Add this new table type, and allow connecting them by refenece.

Signed-off-by: Paul Blakey <paulb@mellanox.com>
Reviewed-by: Oz Shlomo <ozsh@mellanox.com>
